
<p>
	The U.S. Treasury classified bitcoin as a convertible decentralized virtual currency in 2013. The Commodity Futures Trading Commission, CFTC, classified bitcoin as a commodity in September 2015. Per IRS, bitcoin is taxed as a property.
</p>
<p>
	Notes for startups:
	<ul>		
		<li>political climate: moderately friendly;</li>
		<li>economic climate: moderately encouraging;</li>
		<li>regions to focus: the World;</li>
		<li>industries to focus: all;</li>
		<li>major limitations: extensive legal requirements and high costs;</li>
		<li>stimulus: ... ;</li>
		<li>opportunities: building multinational business;</li>
		<li>Cryptocurrencies and ICOs (outlook): legal (moderately positive).</li>
	</ul>
